!iflang [english]

!begin_node Cookie, _MCH

!label Machine type
!label Hardware, non-ST-compatible
!label Computer family
(!B)Machine type(!b)

The upper word describes the computer family, the lower serves for 
finer distinctions.

!begin_table [l|l|l]
High !! Low !! Type
!hline
0 !! 0  !! Atari-ST  (260-ST,520-ST,1040-ST,Mega-ST,...)
1 !! 0  !! Atari-STE (1040-STE, ST-Book)
1 !! 16 !! Mega-STE
2 !! 0  !! Atari-TT
3 !! 0  !! Atari-Falcon030
4 !! 0  !! Milan
5 !! 0  !! ARAnyM
!end_table

The lower word serves for finer distinctions, and is at present 
defined only for the STE models. This can be:

0x001 = ST-Book (!nl)
0x008 = STE with IDE hardware (!nl)
0x100 = Sparrow (Falcon pre-production machine)

If the value is -1, then it's a case of non-ST-compatible hardware. 
In that case all hardware accesses should be avoided.

For the Medusa T40 there is: (!nl)
0x00004D34 without SCSI (!nl)
0x00024D34 with SCSI

!end_node

